1
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,400
Two chocolates.

2
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:38,240
Call.

3
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:11,340
Let's show.

4
00:01:21,880 --> 00:01:22,680
Continue.

5
00:01:34,039 --> 00:01:35,200
Only 5,000?

6
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:37,640
Raise you 20,000.

7
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,210
I'll bet 50,000.

8
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,240
That's more like it.

9
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,000
Call, call.

10
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,660
His hole card is a four.

11
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:55,940
Then I'll show.

12
00:01:56,960 --> 00:01:57,640
King.

13
00:01:58,520 --> 00:01:59,800
Thanks, Officer Shao.

14
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:04,290
That must be another ten years of your salary.

15
00:02:39,320 --> 00:02:41,320
Your luck has been pretty good before.

16
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,480
It's about time I got on a winning streak.

17
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:45,000
Go ahead.

18
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:47,700
You should've toughened up earlier.

19
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,040
Okay.

20
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:52,960
All in.

21
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:56,920
I'll call.

22
00:02:59,079 --> 00:02:59,940
Three of a kind.

23
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,680
That's indeed a big hand.

24
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:09,240
But I also have three of a kind.

25
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,600
Three plus two.

26
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,040
A full house.

27
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,120
You used to be a cop,

28
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:16,920
and you suppressed me.

29
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,160
I couldn't beat you.

30
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,280
But now this cop

31
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,500
is useless.

32
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:24,840
See the guest out.

33
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,480
Wait a minute.

34
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,920
What's wrong, Officer Shao?

35
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,400
I haven't lost everything yet.

36
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,960
How can this game be over?

37
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:37,720
You're out of chips.

38
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,640
Gambling is risky.

39
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,240
Yes, you have a point.

40
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,560
How about I keep 3,000 for gas first?

41
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,280
Sorry.

42
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,560
I was being presumptuous.

43
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,720
Come on, 3,000.

44
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,320
Come on.

45
00:04:39,280 --> 00:04:40,740
Shao Yu's hole card is an A.

46
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:41,800
Three of a kind.

47
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,640
Let's see.

48
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:46,080
Officer Shao, we can wrap this up.

49
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,320
From the cards on the table,

50
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,640
you don't have much of a chance.

51
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:53,760
What if my hole card is a 5 or a Q?

52
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,320
You are out of money.

53
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:57,180
How about this?

54
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:57,960
Let's

55
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,320
seal the cards first.

56
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:03,440
You go back and mortgage your house too.

57
00:05:03,440 --> 00:05:04,440
I'll wait for you.

58
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:05,200
No need.

59
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,600
That's too much trouble.

60
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:08,130
I have something to bet.

61
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:11,680
What else do you have to bet?

62
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,920
Are you really betting her?

63
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,400
Didn't you say before

64
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:29,280
that you'd pay 100,000 for a night with her?

65
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,960
I'll let her accompany you for a year.

66
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:32,720
10 million.

67
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,100
I bet on this round.

68
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,240
Is she gold-plated?

69
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,240
10 million.

70
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,120
But if you put it that way,

71
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,840
I really do like this girl more and more.

72
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:45,040
All right, it's a bet.

73
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,000
Officer Shao.

74
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,040
Even if your hole card is a Queen,

75
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,760
you still can't beat me.

76
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,600
Just give up.

77
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:08,920
But if your hole card is a 5...

78
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,140
It's possible.

79
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,440
But...

80
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,640
But what?

81
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,060
But my hole card can't possibly be a 5, right?

82
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,920
Why are you so confident?

83
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:21,240
Because you know my hole card is an Ace.

84
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,800
Sorry.

85
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,880
My hole card

86
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:26,880
is 5.

87
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,720
Four of a kind.

88
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,080
When I was a police officer,

89
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:38,520
I worked undercover in an underground casino.

90
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,760
I know all

91
00:06:40,159 --> 00:06:40,890
your tricks.

92
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,140
When we started playing mahjong,

93
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:47,460
you could actually see our tiles through the monitors.

94
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:50,200
Everything is in your control.

95
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:52,520
The dealer's hand is a flush, winning on a 6-character.

96
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:55,280
The next player's hand is all triplets, winning on a 4-dot.

97
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:56,760
The opposite player's hand is a straight,

98
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:58,520
waiting solely for an 8-character.

99
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,040
Then you used various cheating tricks

100
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,240
to let us win a little.

101
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:05,840
You gave us a taste of winning first

102
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,080
to lure us into the big game.

103
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:10,800
Mahjong.

104
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:12,560
I won too.

105
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,440
Me too.

106
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,720
And when playing blackjack,

107
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:19,400
you rigged the dealing shoe.

108
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:23,160
The cards will follow your pre-set program

109
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:24,880
when dealt to the others.

110
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,000
No matter who the dealer is,

111
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,730
you will always get good cards.

112
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,360
Sorry, blackjack again.

113
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,290
Because of the rules of blackjack,

114
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:36,640
you can't completely control the others' minds,

115
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:39,200
so you can't guarantee that the cards you set up

116
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,040
will definitely end up in your hands.

117
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,400
Your hand is good enough.

118
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,560
The dealer probably can't beat you.

119
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,120
Lao Zhang, enough.

120
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,180
18 is close enough.

121
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:53,960
If anything unexpected happens,

122
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:56,440
your people will analyze the remaining cards

123
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,520
and provide the best solution.

124
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:58,920
Li Si, keep hitting

125
00:07:58,920 --> 00:07:59,780
until you bust.

126
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:00,960
Hit.

127
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:05,900
Wang Wu,

128
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,480
whether Brother Hui hits or not,

129
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,640
you both stop hitting.

130
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,240
Stand.

131
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,280
What the hell?

132
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,840
Standing on 12?

133
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:13,570
Play it safe.

134
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,520
They relay instructions to your two shills through earpieces,

135
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,580
sacrificing them.

136
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,520
To ensure that in this round

137
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:21,320
you can get the cards designed earlier.

138
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:23,080
It's 20.

139
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:31,080
No wonder you didn't lose any money when playing just now.

140
00:08:32,760 --> 00:08:35,039
When I was the dealer, you bet less.

141
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,640
When someone else was the dealer,

142
00:08:39,640 --> 00:08:41,080
you followed my bet.

143
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,720
But I have a question.

144
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,120
How did you do that?

145
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:00,640
Simple.

146
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:05,000
I have this thing too.

147
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,120
And your card shuffler at the critical moment

148
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,240
is no longer under your control.

149
00:09:14,880 --> 00:09:16,080
Hello, Brother Shao.

150
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:16,920
Do me a favor.

151
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,410
I had someone hack into your system

152
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,380
and control the shuffler.

153
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:26,760
Brother Hui, his hole card is an Ace.

154
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,970
You thought you dealt me an Ace.

155
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:32,680
Unfortunately, that's only what you saw on the computer.

156
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,160
How dare you cheat!

157
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,160
All right.

158
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,760
I'll be taking this money.

159
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,480
If I remember correctly,

160
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:11,360
I won 10,003,000.

161
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,280
Keep the 3,000.

162
00:10:13,560 --> 00:10:16,160
Buy your little brother something good to eat.

163
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,840
I've been running this casino for a long time,

164
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:20,500
and I always accept my losses.

165
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,240
But you just admitted

166
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,280
that you cheated too.

167
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,560
The money you won by cheating,

168
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:31,840
how can I give it to you?

169
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,120
I did cheat.

170
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:35,520
But you cheated too.

171
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:38,440
So we're even, okay?

172
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:40,850
According to our rules.

173
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,280
Take this one million principal

174
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,440
back.

175
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,800
Did I just say

176
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:50,040
I hacked into your system?

177
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,920
The footage captured by all these cameras

178
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,880
is on my friend's computer.

179
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,440
If I give it to the police...

180
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:00,880
If you give it to the police, you're in it too.

181
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:02,410
So what do you want to do?

182
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:04,450
Give me a chance to turn the tables.

183
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:12,960
Okay.

184
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:15,320
But

185
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,280
how we play

186
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:18,760
is up to me.

187
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,760
I'll take 4 million out of this 10 million.

188
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,960
I'll play the remaining 6 million with you.

189
00:11:23,960 --> 00:11:24,960
If you win,

190
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,000
this 6 million

191
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:26,960
is yours.

192
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,000
If you lose,

193
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,040
this 6 million is also yours.

194
00:11:31,040 --> 00:11:31,760
But

195
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,540
you must answer a question for me.

196
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:36,780
What question?

197
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,280
You definitely know the answer to this question.

198
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:41,520
And I won't make it too difficult for you.

199
00:11:41,520 --> 00:11:43,280
Thinking about it, I seem

200
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:45,080
to be at a slight disadvantage.

201
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,960
I have to take this four million.

202
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,920
Didn't I just say

203
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,360
that I've hacked into your system?

204
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,520
With footage from so many cameras,

205
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:55,080
imagine if I gave it to the police.

206
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:55,680
Fine.

207
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:56,920
How do we bet?

208
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:59,680
We don't trust each other right now.

209
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,540
How about this.

210
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,330
We just leave it to luck.

211
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,240
We'll still play Blackjack.

212
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:04,840
But

213
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:06,810
we can't play it ourselves.

214
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,400
We'll let someone else play for us.

215
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,640
And they have to be blindfolded.

216
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,120
They can't look at the cards.

217
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,120
Winning or losing

218
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,000
is entirely up to heaven.

219
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,410
I can even make another concession

220
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,840
and let you be the dealer.

221
00:12:19,960 --> 00:12:22,280
A tie means I lose, too.

222
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,920
Sister Hai, do you want more?

223
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,300
What about you?

224
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:27,640
Want more?

225
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,240
Do you want more?

226
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,240
Want more?

227
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,120
I admit defeat.

228
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:23,920
I accept it.

229
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,280
Officer Shao.

230
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:26,600
Ask away.

231
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,080
When I was a cop,

232
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,280
I had an informant named Mr. Bai.

233
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:37,050
You should know him.

234
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,120
Sang Rong killed him.

235
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,000
What I want to ask is,

236
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,920
who leaked his identity as an informant?

237
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:52,760
Fine.

238
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,560
It's been so long.

239
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:58,090
It doesn't matter if I tell you.

240
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:02,640
Actually, we had no idea he was your informant.

241
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,320
The reason Lao Bai was killed

242
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,080
was because he...

243
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:12,450
was because he broke a major taboo in the underworld.

244
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:14,410
He seduced the boss's wife.

245
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:16,850
He slept with Brother Rong's wife.

246
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:20,720
Impossible. Then Mr. Bai...

247
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,920
Officer Shao.

248
00:15:23,440 --> 00:15:26,160
I only entered the answer to one question.

249
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:14,440
Lighting crew.
